documentType: evidence inventory and chain of custody form
summary: This document is an FBI evidence inventory and chain of custody record (FD-1087) for items seized in case 31E-MM-108062. It lists various evidence items including audio tapes, photos, and papers, and tracks custody transfers from 2006 to 2021. The evidence appears to be related to a Palm Beach Police Department investigation.

locations: Palm Beach, Florida (inferred from PBPD evidence tags)
keyFacts: The evidence is from FBI case 31E-MM-108062 and includes materials originally from Palm Beach Police Department (PBPD) case numbers (e.g., 05-237, 05-243).
Evidence items include multiple audio tapes, a photo line-up, CDs, and various papers containing flight information, phone numbers, and initials (e.g., N.M., G.M., J.B., C.W.).
The chain of custody shows the evidence was collected on August 28, 2006, and was still being tracked as of July 20, 2021, with a note that the evidence log was missing.
The evidence was held at different FBI offices over time, specifically New York and Miami.
